# ShopMate Android Project Structure

## Architecture

ShopMate follows the MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel) architecture pattern:

- **Model**: Data classes in `app/src/main/java/com/example/shopmate/data/model/`
- **View**: Activities and Fragments in `app/src/main/java/com/example/shopmate/ui/`
- **ViewModel**: ViewModels in `app/src/main/java/com/example/shopmate/viewmodel/`

## Key Components

- **Activities**: UI entry points in `app/src/main/java/com/example/shopmate/ui/activities/`
- **Fragments**: UI components in `app/src/main/java/com/example/shopmate/ui/fragments/`
- **Adapters**: RecyclerView adapters in `app/src/main/java/com/example/shopmate/ui/adapters/`
- **Repositories**: Data sources in `app/src/main/java/com/example/shopmate/data/repository/`
- **Network**: API interfaces in `app/src/main/java/com/example/shopmate/data/network/`
- **Utils**: Helper classes in `app/src/main/java/com/example/shopmate/util/`

## Main Entry Point

The main application class is `ShopMateApplication.java` which initializes app-wide components.
